&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Foot and Ankle Fellow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Trauma and Orthopaedics &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harrogate NHS Foundation Trust is seeking to appoint 2 x Clinical Foot and Ankle Fellows in the department of Trauma and Orthopaedics on a fixed term basis.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 x 6 month posts available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post 1 - April 2021 - October 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post 2 - October 2021 - April 2022&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts will involve outpatient sessions and the successful applicants will join a team of Consultants and a dynamic medical and nursing team. Please note, FRCS (Trauma and Orthopaedics) or equivalent is an essential requirement for this post. Additionally, CCT or CESR would be desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There may be opportunities to facilitate independent clinics and theatre lists. Any available options will be explored further, following a review of the successful candidate’s skill set and level of experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prospective applicants are encouraged to visit the hospital to meet our teams and experience the way we work. For more information and to arrange an informal visit, please contact Mr David Lavalette by email at &lt;span&gt;david.lavalette@nhs.net &lt;/span&gt;or Mr Mark Farndon at &lt;span&gt;mfarndon@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;. Should you have any queries regarding the application process, please contact Medical Staffing via &lt;span&gt;hdft.medicalworkforce@nhs.net.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
